*Consequence:* The PDH cascade is the most objectively measurable in the chapter ‚ÄĒ lactate is quantifiable with a \$50 handheld meter. The diagnostic sequence: (1) measure resting and exertional lactate; (2) LDN trial ‚Üí lactate reduction = inflammatory PDK; (3) thiamine trial ‚Üí lactate reduction = cofactor deficiency; (4) pyridostigmine trial ‚Üí lactate reduction = perfusion deficit; (5) DCA trial ‚Üí definitive test of PDH phosphorylation as rate-limiting. The combination of lactate measurement + drug probes converts PDH tracing from subjective symptom report to pharmacometabolic assay. A patient who produces lactate above 4 mmol/L at 50 watts on a stationary bike and drops to 2 mmol/L on thiamine has had their PDH cofactor status measured without a muscle biopsy.
*Origin:* mechanistic-pathway-tracing.

=== Acquired Ischemic Mitochondrial Myopathy (AIMM) / Na‚Āļ-Ca¬≤‚Āļ Cascade
<sec:aimm-cascade>

*Certainty: 0.40.* NHE1‚ÜíNCX1‚Üímitochondrial Ca¬≤‚Āļ overload cascade documented in ischemia-reperfusion injury (cardiac and skeletal muscle). AIMM = acquired ischemic mitochondrial myopathy ‚ÄĒ the concept proposed by Scheibenbogen and Wirth that repeated microvascular ischemia-reperfusion episodes in skeletal muscle cause cumulative mitochondrial structural damage, producing the PEM phenotype. MDC002/Mitodicure is a dual NHE1 + NCLX modulator in preclinical development for ME/CFS.

==== Cascade: Hypoperfusion ‚Üí Na‚Āļ overload ‚Üí mitochondrial Ca¬≤‚Āļ ‚Üí mPTP ‚Üí PEM

*Cascade:*
- Capillary hypoperfusion (endothelial dysfunction, microclots, RBC deformability loss)
- Ischemia during exertion ‚Üí anaerobic metabolism ‚Üí intracellular acidosis
